# ============================================================================
# API Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Backend API URL
# - Local development: http://localhost:8000
# - Production: https://your-backend-name.onrender.com
# - Replace with your actual backend URL after deployment

REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# ============================================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. REACT_APP_ PREFIX:
#    - All custom environment variables in React MUST start with REACT_APP_
#    - This is a Create React App convention for security
#    - Without this prefix, the variable won't be available
#
# 2. USAGE IN CODE:
#    - Access in code: process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL
#    - Example:
#      const apiUrl = process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL || 'http://localhost:8000';
#
# 3. WHEN VARIABLES ARE LOADED:
#    - Environment variables are embedded during BUILD time
#    - If you change .env, you must rebuild the app:
#      npm run build
#
# 4. DIFFERENT ENVIRONMENTS:
#    - .env.local: Local development (npm start)
#    - .env.production: Production build (npm run build)
#    - .env.test: Test environment (npm test)
#
# 5. SECURITY:
#    - NEVER commit .env files with real values to Git
#    - .env files should be in .gitignore
#    - Only commit .env.example (template with no secrets)
#    - Never put API keys or passwords in environment variables
#      that are embedded in the frontend (they're visible to users!)
#
# 6. DEPLOYMENT ON RENDER:
#    - Set environment variables in Render dashboard
#    - Go to Static Site â†’ Environment
#    - Add: REACT_APP_API_URL = your backend URL
#    - Redeploy after adding variables
#
# ============================================================================
# EXAMPLES
# ============================================================================
#
# Local Development:
# REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
#
# Production (Render):
# REACT_APP_API_URL=https://image-classification-backend.onrender.com
#
# Production (Custom Domain):
# REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
#
# ============================================================================
